                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/4416</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Press Release Issued by the Department of State, January 9,
                        1937</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1937-01-09">January 9, 1937</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>In answer to inquiries at press conference, Acting Secretary of State R. Walton
                    Moore said: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>I do not think the reports coming in from Europe should cause undue
                            alarm. I decline to believe that any war involving the leading European
                            nations is about to occur. I decline to believe that any such adventure
                            in suicide is imminent. On the contrary I am convinced that the leaders
                            of those nations, knowing what a perhaps fatal blow another extensive
                            war would be to the fabric of European civilization, will find some
                            common sense methods of adjusting all controversies. Of course all the
                            world would be glad to see the civil strife in Spain wholly
                            localized.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
